metadata.name: Traveler #22
metadata.description:
Retro sci-fi style landscape sketch drawn by code.

Features:
- Terrain: Cliff, Cavern, Sky, Megalopolis, Desert, Sea, Space, Volcano
- Orientation: Landscape, Portlait
- Palette: White, Cream, Tan, Pink, Green, Yellow, Orange
- Background: Light, Dark

Live view options:
- Press "s" key: Saves the high resolution image (4200 x 3300 for landscape, 3300 x 4200 for portlait)

Depending on the device you run it on, it may take some time for the drawing to complete.
Made with p5js.

June 2022
ykxotkx

metadata.name: Collapse #158
metadata.description:
The Impossibility of Representing Something Spherical Flat

A sphere collapses to a flat plane, revealing the transformations and stretching required for such an operation. How to represent something spherical flat? How to see what's not there, or how to see it differently? 

Released on the occasion of the Tribute to Herbert W. Franke.  
50% of the primary sales will be donated to the Foundation Herbert W. Franke.

metadata.name: Candy World #18
metadata.description:
Candy World, is a place where life is sweet, minimal, essential. 
Colours are bright and solid, shapes are well defined and you can get away from the city into a nice park in mountains. 
Joy and happiness irradiate from the sky. 
There is no crime, no violence, and no conflict. Everyone is happy and content. 
Candy World is an empty world because no one lives there.

- hit 's' to save .svg
- hit 'p' to save .png

metadata.name: ____ - Iteration 3 #506
metadata.description:
This project is part of a larger experiment that explores and celebrates the process of making generative art by progressively releasing iterations, working towards a final release on my main account (tz1RkYY3jr1ocuPdQqrRefr5FqoawKQsmBmD). The iterations will be titled ____ - Iteration 1, ____ - Iteration 2, etc. At this point, the number of iterations has not been determined, but more information will be provided as this experiment unfolds.

The final release will only be made available to those who have collected each iteration (using an allowlist), and will be released for free.

In live mode, add &size=<YOUR_PIXEL_SIZE> to change the pixel size of the image for export (Right click to save). For example, &size=4000 will set the width of the image to be 4000 pixels.

metadata.name: Rehash 10000 #140
metadata.description:
This project was supposed to be released in celebration of fxhash reaching 10,000 projects since its inception, but it's hard to celebrate when war breaks out and innocent people fear for their lives. Please go ahead and mint as many iterations as you like for free. If you feel the art is worth more than 0 tez, you are welcome to donate to the Tezos fund to support our Ukrainian friends (KT1DWnLiUkNtAQDErXxudFEH63JC6mqg3HEx).

Each mint combines 5 of my previous 14 fxhash projects into a drug-induced distorted vision of life in the Metaverse. This artwork is fully generative and was entirely hand-coded in 5333 lines of plain JavaScript code. Forever limited to 500 editions on the Tezos blockchain. London, February 2022.

metadata.name: ACCUMULATOR #110
metadata.description:
A fully procedural and real-time simulated circuit, with 8 oscillating input signals and an output screen!

Each chip stores the incoming signals energy and propagates it to all its connected counterparts.

The animation on the screen is the result of all this accumulated signals.

Features:
 - 4 screen colors
 - 15 screen resolutions (sides can be 4, 8, 16, 32 or 64 pixels)
 - 42% chance for the circuit to be symmetrical on the X-axis
 - 24% chance for Y-axis symmetry only if already X-symmetrical
 - 13.37% chance for a shiny foil overlay
 - different "chipset manufacturer codes" based on PCB and chips color combinations

[Realized in vanilla JS with love and madness]
(everything is procedurally generated)
